68#define AM_DEVICES_510L_RADIO_IPC_MEM_RW_MAX_SIZE (128)
69// OTP INFO1 0x42006970 ~ 0x42006A50 is allocated for RF Trim
70#define AM_DEVICES_510L_RADIO_RF_TRIM_SIZE (0xE0)
71//
73//
74// Note: the IPC share memory includes the IPC TX/RX buffer, vring size, status
75// and necessary memory alignment. The IPC TX/RX buffer number can only be the
76// power of 2, for example, 4, 8, 16. The IPC backend will calcuate the maximum
77// supported buffer number in IPC instance creation based on allocated total IPC
78// memory size. We need to define a right memory size to match with the expected
79// buffer number, otherwise the actual buffer number maybe less than the expected
80// one and cause memory waste.
81//
82// The macro IPC_SHM_SIZE(num, buf_size) can be used to get the matched total IPC
83// memory size.
84#define AM_DEVICES_510L_RADIO_IPC_BUF_NUM (8)
85#define AM_DEVICES_510L_RADIO_IPC_SHM_DEFAULT_SIZE \
86 (IPC_SHM_SIZE(AM_DEVICES_510L_RADIO_IPC_BUF_NUM, RPMSG_BUFFER_SIZE))
